# RoadSense AI Project Report\par
\par
## PART 1: MINI PROJECT\par
\par
## TITLE\par
\par
RoadSense AI: Road Damage Detection with Civic Repair Planning\par
\par
## AIM\par
\par
To select a simple machine learning based road damage detection project, customize it with a novel AI-powered civic repair planning feature, deploy it through an inference API, containerize it, and prepare complete project documentation.\par
\par
## PROBLEM STATEMENT\par
\par
Road damage such as potholes and cracks creates safety risks for drivers, increases vehicle maintenance cost, and makes city infrastructure harder to manage. Manual road inspection requires time, manpower, and repeated field visits. A normal computer vision model can detect damage, but detection alone is not enough for municipal decision making. The maintenance team also needs priority, repair cost, crew planning, response time, and traffic control guidance.\par
\par
RoadSense AI solves this by converting road image analysis into an operational repair plan.\par
\par
## BASE PROJECT SELECTED\par
\par
The base idea is taken from common open-source road damage detection projects that use YOLO-based object detection for pavement defects. The selected use case is intentionally simple compared with heavy projects such as face recognition or PPE kit analysis, but it has strong social impact and clear SDG alignment.\par
\par
The customized project is named RoadSense AI.\par
\par
## NOVELTY ADDED\par
\par
The novelty added to the base project is the Civic Repair Planner.\par
\par
Most detection projects stop after showing bounding boxes. RoadSense AI goes further by generating:\par
\par
- Severity score\par
- Repair priority\par
- Estimated repair cost in INR\par
- Crew size recommendation\par
- SLA response time\par
- Risk zone\par
- Lane closure requirement\par
- SDG alignment\par
- Maintenance dispatch note\par
\par
This makes the project a full software product rather than only a model demo.\par
\par
## SDG ALIGNMENT\par
\par
RoadSense AI is aligned with:\par
\par
- SDG 3: Good Health and Well-Being, because better road maintenance reduces accident risk.\par
- SDG 9: Industry, Innovation and Infrastructure, because the project supports intelligent infrastructure inspection.\par
- SDG 11: Sustainable Cities and Communities, because it helps cities maintain safer roads.\par
