## API ENDPOINTS\par
\par
| Endpoint | Method | Purpose |\par
|---|---|---|\par
| `/` | GET | Root API response |\par
| `/api/v1/health` | GET | Checks backend and model status |\par
| `/api/v1/detect` | POST | Upload image and receive full result |\par
| `/api/v1/analyze` | POST | Upload image and receive analytics only |\par
| `/api/v1/plan` | POST | Generate repair plan from manual detections |\par
\par
## PROCEDURE\par
\par
1. A road damage detection use case was selected for the mini project.\par
2. A FastAPI backend was created.\par
3. Image upload support was added using `python-multipart`.\par
4. OpenCV was used for image decoding and annotation.\par
5. ONNX Runtime was added as the model serving engine.\par
6. Demo mode was added to make the project runnable without a trained model file.\par
7. Severity scoring and repair priority classification were implemented.\par
8. Civic Repair Planner was added as the novelty component.\par
9. A frontend dashboard was created for image upload and result display.\par
10. Dockerfiles were created for backend and frontend.\par
11. Docker Compose was configured for full-stack execution.\par
12. Kubernetes deployment YAML was prepared.\par
13. Git was used for version control.\par
14. The project was pushed to GitHub.\par
